      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That makes sense from a systemic viewpoint. But if we look at the actual data, the correlation between specific ethnicities and crime rates remains high regardless of the neighborhood. Some researchers argue that systemic bias doesn't fully account for the gap. Can you look at the more controversial arguments that suggest there are cultural or behavioral patterns within certain groups that contribute to these higher rates? I'm looking for a balanced view for my paper.",
